---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="HeadGenome" description="Attention heads are not interchangeable. We mapped what each one does — across 1,568 heads and four architectures.">

<!-- ── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="landing-hero">
  <div class="hero-text">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">Nature · Vol. 2025</p>
    <h1>Attention heads are&nbsp;<br/>not interchangeable.</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      We classified every attention head in four transformer architectures
      into one of four functional types — using nothing but the model's own behaviour.
      The taxonomy is <strong>universal</strong>, <strong>architecture-intrinsic</strong>,
      and <strong>actionable</strong>.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href={`${base}/taxonomy`} class="btn-primary">Explore the findings →</a>
      <a href={`${base}/explorer`} class="btn-secondary">Head Explorer</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Live atlas canvas -->
  <div class="atlas-wrap reveal">
    <canvas id="atlas-canvas" role="img" aria-label="HeadGenome atlas: 1568 attention heads coloured by type"></canvas>
    <p class="atlas-caption">1,568 heads · 4 architectures · 4 functional classes</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── HEADLINE STATS ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section">
  <p class="overline reveal">The four headline results</p>
  <div class="stat-grid">
    <div class="stat-card c-blue reveal">
      <div class="stat-num">1,568</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Attention heads classified across GPT-2, Qwen-0.5B, Qwen-1.5B & Llama-3.2-1B</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-purple reveal" style="animation-delay:.07s">
      <div class="stat-num">96.5%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Retrieval + Induction co-ablation recovery — <em>zero</em> recovery with either class alone</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-orange reveal" style="animation-delay:.14s">
      <div class="stat-num">13.3×</div>
      <div class="stat-label">KV-cache compression on Llama-3.2-1B (measured, not projected)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-red reveal" style="animation-delay:.21s">
      <div class="stat-num">p≈10⁻¹²⁷</div>
      <div class="stat-label">V/Q ratio scaling law significance — across all four architectures</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── PLAIN-ENGLISH EXPLAINER ───────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section section-dark">
  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="overline">What is a head?</p>
      <h2>Transformers have eyes. We mapped what they're looking at.</h2>
      <p>
        Every transformer layer has dozens of <strong>attention heads</strong>. Each head decides
        which tokens to "look at" when processing each word. The standard assumption is
        that heads are interchangeable — you can prune any one of them with similar cost.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem">
        HeadGenome shows this is wrong. The same four functional types emerge <em>independently</em>
        in every architecture we tested — determined entirely by what the head learned to do,
        not what it was told to do.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="type-cards reveal">
      <div class="type-card">
        <span class="pill pill-sink">● Sink</span>
        <p>Absorbs residual attention mass. Targets punctuation and the first token. Structurally inert.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <span class="pill pill-local">● Local</span>
        <p>Attends to a sliding window of nearby tokens. The backbone of positional context. 81–86% of all heads.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <span class="pill pill-retrieval">● Retrieval</span>
        <p>Reaches anywhere in the sequence to retrieve semantically relevant past tokens. Critical for recall.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <span class="pill pill-induction">● Induction</span>
        <p>Copies retrieved content forward in the residual stream. The execution engine for retrieval.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── NAVIGATION DOORS ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section">
  <p class="overline reveal">Choose your depth</p>
  <div class="doors reveal">
    <a href={`${base}/taxonomy`} class="door">
      <span class="door-icon">📐</span>
      <strong>What did we find?</strong>
      <p>The V/Q scaling law, bifurcation axis, and the HeadGenome atlas</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}/universality`} class="door">
      <span class="door-icon">🌐</span>
      <strong>How sure are we?</strong>
      <p>Untrained controls, permutation nulls, and cross-architecture proof</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}/causal`} class="door">
      <span class="door-icon">⚡</span>
      <strong>Do they actually matter?</strong>
      <p>Ablation studies, co-gating circuits, the perplexity illusion</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}/systems`} class="door">
      <span class="door-icon">🚀</span>
      <strong>Why does this matter?</strong>
      <p>13.3× KV-cache compression and projected 4–8× FLOP savings</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}/explorer`} class="door door-highlight">
      <span class="door-icon">🔬</span>
      <strong>Explore it yourself</strong>
      <p>Browse all 1,568 heads by model, layer, and class</p>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<!-- ── ATLAS CANVAS ANIMATION ───────────────────────────────── -->
<script>
  const base = document.querySelector('base')?.href ?? '';
  fetch('/attentionheadgenome/canonical_labels.json')
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(data => {
      const canvas = document.getElementById('atlas-canvas');
      if (!canvas) return;
      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

      const C = { sink: '#ef4444', local: '#3b82f6', retrieval: '#a855f7', induction: '#f97316' };

      // Build flat list of heads with target positions
      const heads = [];
      const models = Object.entries(data.models);
      const modelCount = models.length;

      models.forEach(([name, mdata], mi) => {
        const nlayers = mdata.n_layers;
        const nheads = mdata.n_heads ?? (Object.keys(mdata.heads).length / nlayers);
        
        Object.entries(mdata.heads).forEach(([key, hd]) => {
          const layer = hd.layer;
          const hidx = hd.head_idx;
          heads.push({
            label: hd.label,
            tx: ((mi + 0.5) / modelCount) + (hidx / (nheads * modelCount * 0.9)) - 0.02,
            ty: (layer + 0.5) / nlayers,
            x: Math.random(), y: Math.random(),
            color: C[hd.label] || '#94a3b8'
          });
        });
      });

      let animFrame = 0;
      const totalFrames = 90;
      let raf;

      function resize() {
        const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
        const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
        canvas.width = rect.width * dpr;
        canvas.height = rect.height * dpr;
        ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
      }
      resize();
      window.addEventListener('resize', () => { resize(); animFrame = 0; });

      function ease(t) { return t < 0.5 ? 2*t*t : -1+(4-2*t)*t; }

      function draw() {
        const w = canvas.getBoundingClientRect().width;
        const h = canvas.getBoundingClientRect().height;
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
        const p = Math.min(animFrame / totalFrames, 1);
        const ep = ease(p);

        heads.forEach(hd => {
          const x = (hd.x + (hd.tx - hd.x) * ep) * w;
          const y = (hd.y + (hd.ty - hd.y) * ep) * h;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(x, y, 3.5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
          ctx.fillStyle = hd.color + (p < 1 ? Math.floor(200 + 55 * p).toString(16) : '');
          ctx.fill();
        });

        animFrame++;
        if (animFrame <= totalFrames + 10) raf = requestAnimationFrame(draw);
      }

      // Start when visible
      const obs = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
        if (entries[0].isIntersecting) { animFrame = 0; draw(); obs.disconnect(); }
      });
      obs.observe(canvas);
    })
    .catch(() => {}); // graceful - canvas just stays empty
</script>

<style>
/* ── Landing-specific styles ──── */
.landing-hero {
  min-height: 100vh;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center;
  padding: 8rem 2.5rem 4rem;
  max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; gap: 4rem;
}
@media (min-width: 900px) {
  .landing-hero { flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }
}
.hero-text { flex: 1; max-width: 580px; }
.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: .8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .12em;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--local); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}
.landing-hero h1 {
  font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.04em; line-height: 1.05;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}
.landing-hero h1 em { color: var(--local); font-style: normal; }
.hero-sub {
  font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.7;
}
.hero-sub strong { color: var(--text); }
.hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

.btn-primary {
  background: var(--local); color: white;
  padding: .75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 2rem;
  text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: .95rem;
  transition: opacity .2s, transform .2s;
  display: inline-block;
}
.btn-primary:hover { opacity: .85; transform: translateY(-2px); }
.btn-secondary {
  border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text);
  padding: .75rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 2rem;
  text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; font-size: .95rem;
  transition: background .2s;
}
.btn-secondary:hover { background: var(--faint); }

.atlas-wrap { flex: 1; min-width: 300px; }
.atlas-caption {
  text-align: center; font-size: .8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: .75rem;
}

.section-dark { background: var(--bg2); }
.two-col {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem;
  max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 5rem 2.5rem;
}
@media (min-width: 760px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; align-items: start; } }
.two-col h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -.03em; margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.two-col p { color: var(--muted); }
.type-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
.type-card {
  background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
}
.type-card .pill { margin-bottom: .5rem; }
.type-card p { font-size: .88rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; }

.overline {
  font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .1em;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; display: block;
}

.doors {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1rem;
}
.door {
  background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
  text-decoration: none; color: var(--text);
  transition: transform .2s, box-shadow .2s, border-color .2s;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .5rem;
}
.door:hover { transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.25); border-color: var(--local); }
.door-highlight { border-color: var(--local); }
.door-icon { font-size: 1.6rem; }
.door strong { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; }
.door p { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; }
</style>
